text.tspan: The archivist needs to keep his data forever, searchable and organized. This
ensures that important data is not lost when the original site is destroyed
because of neglect, censorship or catastrophes.
The archivist might also be storing data on Archive.org or Archive.is for
redundancy purposes, but does not trust those services to be around forever
and prefer to also store data locally. What is important is that the archived links
(S)He also uses Zotero to index their physical media collection.
Free software and privacy are important, but not an absolute.
The archivist would love having wallabag to keep real archives of registered
links, as standard WARC files (with attachments). (S)He would also love to see
really improved extraction capabilities. Like the blogger, the wallabag search
and data organization features are really important.
wallabag is where I keep all the important links I found
